==English==
===Etymology===
Formed from Latin [[aestivare]], from [[aestus]] ‘heat’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ˌi:stɪ'veɪʃən/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===
'''aestivation'''
# ''(obsolete)'' the spending or passing of a summer
# ''(zoology)'' spending a summer in a state of reduced metabolic activity; the summer version of [[hibernation]]
# ''(botany)'' the arrangement of the parts of a flower inside a bud

===Alternative spellings===
*[[estivation]]

